comment: The value of a finite set of sequential integers. E.g., ` 2 ... 5 ` means the set ` { 2 , 3 , 4 , 5 } ` . A special case of this definition (starting at 1) appears as Definition 11-2.1 of [Gleason] p. 141, where ` NN ` _k means our ` 1 ... k ` ; he calls these sets _segments_ of the integers.
